AS PASSED SENATE
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Part 15 of Article 6 of Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia
2 Annotated, relating to miscellaneous provisions under the "Quality Basic Education Act,"
3 so as to require that local school systems offer certain exams to home study students; to
4 provide for notice requirements; to prohibit additional qualifications; to provide a definition;
5 to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Part 15 of Article 6 of Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
9 relating to miscellaneous provisions under the "Quality Basic Education Act," is amended
10 by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
11 "20-2-324.8.
12 (a) As used in this Code section, the term 'home study student' means a student in grades
13 six through 12 who is in a home study program that meets the requirements of
14 subsection (c) of Code Section 20-2-690.
15 (b) Each local school system that offers the PSAT/NMSQT, SAT, PreACT, or ACT or an
16 advanced placement exam to students enrolled in such local school system shall:
