17 (1) Make each such test or exam available to any home study student who resides in the
18 local school system; and
19 (2) Post on its public website notice of the date that each such test or exam will be
20 administered. Such notice shall include registration dates and procedures and shall state
21 that such test or exam is available for home study students who reside in the local school
22 system.
23 (c) No local school system that offers the PSAT/NMSQT, SAT, PreACT, or ACT or an
24 advanced placement exam to students enrolled in such local school system shall require
25 home study students to pay a fee not required of students enrolled in such local school
26 system or impose any requirement that conflicts with or is in addition to the requirements
27 of subsection (c) of Code Section 20-2-690."
28 SECTION 2.
29 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
